## Config (.env.bug_intake)


BUG_INTAKE_CHANNEL=gmail
BUG_INTAKE_GMAIL_LABEL=Bug Reports
BUG_INTAKE_GMAIL_CREDENTIALS_PATH=./secrets/credentials.json
BUG_INTAKE_GMAIL_TOKEN_PATH=./secrets/token.json
BUG_INTAKE_GITHUB_REPO=owner/repo
BUG_INTAKE_LOG_PATH=./.bug-intake/processing_log.json
BUG_INTAKE_PENDING_ISSUES_DIR=./.bug-intake/pending_issues
BUG_INTAKE_REQUIRE_APPROVAL_FOR_REPLIES=true


---

## Processing Log

Stores:

- message_id
- action
- notes
- github.issue_number
- github.issue_url
- notification status

---

## Architecture (v1 + future ready)


Channel → Normalized Message → Agent → Action → Log → Feedback


### v1 implementations:
- Channel: Gmail
- Issue Provider: GitHub (via gh CLI)
- Agent: Cursor Skill

### Future:
- Slack / Teams adapters
- Claude / OpenAI agents
- Jira / Linear providers

---

## Key Design Principles

- Local-first (no hosted backend)
- Transparent (everything logged)
- Idempotent (no duplicate actions)
- Human-in-loop (no silent replies)
- Extensible (adapter-based design)

---

## Success Criteria

A user can:

- Install package
- Run init
- Fetch Gmail bugs
- Create GitHub issue via Cursor
- Reply to a vague bug
- Ignore a non-bug
- Notify reporter after fix

